extends ../templates/code_preview.pug

block title
	|Autocomplete Identifier Bookmarklet
block head
	style.
		 #javascriptExample{display:none} 
		#headPreview{display:none}

block intro
	p.
		WCAG 2.1 success criteria 1.3.5 states that the purpose of each text box should be noted in the code.  This is commonly done via the autocomplete attibute.
		Unfortunately there isn't an easy way to determine if this attribute has been set without viewing the code.
		This bookmarket will display the value of the autocomplete  attribute next to the text box.

block gitHubLink
	p 
		+github('https://gist.github.com/dobe0002/b2f1ba02e88646e458c5e51cbbc4b379') View code on Github
		
block content
	h2 Description
	p This is simple bookmark will display the value of the autocomplete values so you don't have to view the HMTL code. 

	p.button-row
		a.btn.btn-secondary#bookmarklet(href="")
			| Autocomplete identifier bookmarklet

	+bookmarkInstillation

	



	div#javascriptExample(data-language='language-javascript' data-language-label="Javascript").

